      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      NRPPositiveInteger getBwpFlowIndex()
      The index i=1,2,...,n is used to index the Bandwidth Profile Flow among all Bandwidth ProfileFlows that are mapped to a given Envelope
      NRPNaturalNumber getCbs()
      Committed Burst Size that limits the maximum number of bytes available for a burst of framesthat will be declared Green, in bytes,
      NRPNaturalNumber getCir()
      Committed Information Rate that limits the average rate of frames that will be declaredGreen.
      NRPNaturalNumber getCirMax()
      Maximum Committed Information Rate that limits the rate of tokens added to the committed tokenbucket.
      NRPColorMode getColorMode()
      Color Mode that Indicates whether the Color Identifier of the frame is considered by theBandwidth Profile Algorithm.
      NRPNaturalNumber getCouplingFlag()
      Coupling Flag that Determines if overflow Green tokens can be used as Yellow tokens.
      NRPNaturalNumber getEbs()
      Excessive Burst Size that limits the maximum number of bytes available for a burst of framesthat will be declared Yellow, in bytes.
      NRPNaturalNumber getEir()
      Excess Information Rate that limits the average rate of frames that will be declared Yellow, inbits per second.
      NRPNaturalNumber getEirMax()
      Maximum Excess Infor-mation Rate that Limits the rate of tokens added to the excess tokenbucket, in bits per second.
      NRPPositiveInteger getRank()
      Bandwidth prorile flow rank in an associated Envelope.
      NRPNaturalNumber getTokenRequestOffset()
      Adjusts the number of tokens requested for each external interface frame.
